{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TkytfiZTczp6y7HSztGhcr","type":"tool_result","content":"   465→\n   466→// ============================================================\n   467→// FPS + Main loop + Benchmark reporting\n   468→// ============================================================\n   469→const frameTimes = [];\n   470→let lastTime = performance.now();\n   471→const hud = document.getElementById('hud');\n   472→let benchFrame = 0, benchDone = false;\n   473→\n   474→function frame() {\n   475→  const now = performance.now();\n   476→  const dt = now - lastTime;\n   477→  lastTime = now;\n   478→  benchFrame++;\n   479→  if (benchFrame > 30) frameTimes.push(dt);\n   480→  if (frameTimes.length > 200) frameTimes.shift();\n   481→\n   482→  const display = frameTimes.length ? frameTimes : [16.6];\n   483→  const avgMs = display.reduce((a,b) => a+b, 0) / display.length;\n   484→  hud.textContent = `${NUM_BOIDS.toLocaleString()} boids | ${(1000/avgMs).toFixed(0)} fps | ${avgMs.toFixed(1)} ms`;\n   485→\n   486→  if (benchmarkBoids && frameTimes.length >= 120 && !benchDone) {\n   487→    benchDone = true;\n   488→    const sorted = [...frameTimes].sort((a,b) => a - b);\n   489→    const avg = sorted.reduce((a,b) => a+b, 0) / sorted.length;\n   490→    const p99 = sorted[Math.floor(sorted.length * 0.99)];\n   491→    fetch('/api/bench_result', { method: 'POST',\n   492→      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n   493→      body: JSON.stringify({ num_boids: NUM_BOIDS, frames: sorted.length,\n   494→        avg_ms: +avg.toFixed(2), p99_ms: +p99.toFixed(2),\n   495→        min_ms: +sorted[0].toFixed(2), max_ms: +sorted[sorted.length-1].toFixed(2) }),\n   496→    }).catch(() => {});\n   497→    hud.textContent += ' | BENCHMARK COMPLETE';\n   498→  }\n   499→\n   500→\n   501→\n   502→  const eye = [\n   503→    distance * Math.cos(elevation) * Math.sin(azimuth),\n   504→    distance * Math.sin(elevation),\n   505→    distance * Math.cos(elevation) * Math.cos(azimuth),\n   506→  ];\n   507→  const aspect = canvas.width / canvas.height;\n   508→  const proj = perspective(Math.PI / 3, aspect, 1.0, 600);\n   509→  const view = lookAt(eye, [0,0,0], [0,1,0]);\n   510→  const vp = mat4Mul(proj, view);\n   511→\n   512→  const encoder = device.createCommandEncoder();\n   513→  const simSteps = Math.max(1, Math.round(currentParams.simSpeed ?? 1));\n   514→  for (let s = 0; s < simSteps; s++) {\n   515→    simulation.update(encoder, s === simSteps - 1); // stats only on last step\n   516→  }\n   517→  const ar = autoRangeCb.checked;\n   518→  renderer.render(encoder, vp, currentParams.gradientId ?? 0, currentParams.colorSource ?? 0,\n   519→    currentParams.gain ?? 0.5, ar, simulation.autoMin, simulation.autoMax);\n   520→  device.queue.submit([encoder.finish()]);\n   521→  // Async readback of auto-range stats (non-blocking)\n   522→  if (ar) simulation.readStats();\n   523→\n   524→  requestAnimationFrame(frame);\n   525→}\n   526→requestAnimationFrame(frame);\n   527→\n   528→function showError(msg) {\n   529→  document.getElementById('hud').remove();\n   530→  const d = document.createElement('div'); d.id = 'error'; d.textContent = msg;\n   531→  document.body.appendChild(d);\n   532→}\n   533→</script>\n   534→</body>"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7ffa1055-e97b-4b91-bfbd-0531ff2ae3b8","uuid":"2bc2471b-1a7d-45ef-8e8e-71f1d2226ad5","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:00:18.077Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/aaronlemke/AI/Murmuration/index.html","content":"\n// ============================================================\n// FPS + Main loop + Benchmark reporting\n// ============================================================\nconst frameTimes = [];\nlet lastTime = performance.now();\nconst hud = document.getElementById('hud');\nlet benchFrame = 0, benchDone = false;\n\nfunction frame() {\n  const now = performance.now();\n  const dt = now - lastTime;\n  lastTime = now;\n  benchFrame++;\n  if (benchFrame > 30) frameTimes.push(dt);\n  if (frameTimes.length > 200) frameTimes.shift();\n\n  const display = frameTimes.length ? frameTimes : [16.6];\n  const avgMs = display.reduce((a,b) => a+b, 0) / display.length;\n  hud.textContent = `${NUM_BOIDS.toLocaleString()} boids | ${(1000/avgMs).toFixed(0)} fps | ${avgMs.toFixed(1)} ms`;\n\n  if (benchmarkBoids && frameTimes.length >= 120 && !benchDone) {\n    benchDone = true;\n    const sorted = [...frameTimes].sort((a,b) => a - b);\n    const avg = sorted.reduce((a,b) => a+b, 0) / sorted.length;\n    const p99 = sorted[Math.floor(sorted.length * 0.99)];\n    fetch('/api/bench_result', { method: 'POST',\n      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n      body: JSON.stringify({ num_boids: NUM_BOIDS, frames: sorted.length,\n        avg_ms: +avg.toFixed(2), p99_ms: +p99.toFixed(2),\n        min_ms: +sorted[0].toFixed(2), max_ms: +sorted[sorted.length-1].toFixed(2) }),\n    }).catch(() => {});\n    hud.textContent += ' | BENCHMARK COMPLETE';\n  }\n\n\n\n  const eye = [\n    distance * Math.cos(elevation) * Math.sin(azimuth),\n    distance * Math.sin(elevation),\n    distance * Math.cos(elevation) * Math.cos(azimuth),\n  ];\n  const aspect = canvas.width / canvas.height;\n  const proj = perspective(Math.PI / 3, aspect, 1.0, 600);\n  const view = lookAt(eye, [0,0,0], [0,1,0]);\n  const vp = mat4Mul(proj, view);\n\n  const encoder = device.createCommandEncoder();\n  const simSteps = Math.max(1, Math.round(currentParams.simSpeed ?? 1));\n  for (let s = 0; s < simSteps; s++) {\n    simulation.update(encoder, s === simSteps - 1); // stats only on last step\n  }\n  const ar = autoRangeCb.checked;\n  renderer.render(encoder, vp, currentParams.gradientId ?? 0, currentParams.colorSource ?? 0,\n    currentParams.gain ?? 0.5, ar, simulation.autoMin, simulation.autoMax);\n  device.queue.submit([encoder.finish()]);\n  // Async readback of auto-range stats (non-blocking)\n  if (ar) simulation.readStats();\n\n  requestAnimationFrame(frame);\n}\nrequestAnimationFrame(frame);\n\nfunction showError(msg) {\n  document.getElementById('hud').remove();\n  const d = document.createElement('div'); d.id = 'error'; d.textContent = msg;\n  document.body.appendChild(d);\n}\n</script>\n</body>","numLines":70,"startLine":465,"totalLines":536}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01NkqummYwwh9pw9t2cvwjam","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The benchmark uses `requestAnimationFrame` and measures `performance.now()` between frames. At 60Hz display, `requestAnimationFrame` callbacks fire at ~16.67ms intervals, creating a ceiling. Even if the GPU finishes in 1ms, the frame time measured this way will be 16.67ms because rAF waits for the next vsync.\n\nPrevious successful runs must have been on a display with a higher refresh rate (120Hz or 144Hz) where the vsync interval is ~8.3ms or less, so the GPU work was the bottleneck rather than vsync.\n\nOr maybe the display was different. On macOS, if the MacBook lid is open, the built-in display might be 120Hz (ProMotion). If using an external display, it might be 60Hz.\n \nThis is fundamentally a hardware constraint I can't work around from the browser—I can't disable vsync or change the display refresh rate. There are Chrome flags like `--disable-frame-rate-limit` that might help, but I can't modify those from here, and the benchmark's reliance on `requestAnimationFrame` means it's inherently tied to vsync anyway. Let me look at the serve.py configuration to see if there's a different way to set up the benchmark.\n\nLooking at the results more carefully, something doesn't add up: the best performance recorded is 2,097,000 boids, but the binary search in evaluate.py only goes up to HI=500, which translates to a maximum of 500,000 boids. That's a huge discrepancy. Either the evaluate.py script was modified at some point with a higher HI value, or those results came from a different version entirely—though the file is supposedly locked.\n\nThe real problem I'm facing now is that even 1,000 boids is failing, and the consistent 16.7ms frame time across all counts points directly to vsync being locked at 60Hz. That's the bottleneck: each frame takes ~16.7ms, which exceeds the 16.6ms target. I should check the system's display refresh rate and see if there's any way to adjust the display settings or detect if an external monitor is connected.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1578,"cache_read_input_tokens":57630,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1578},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7ffa1055-e97b-4b91-bfbd-0531ff2ae3b8","uuid":"a6fee8af-3a5d-4a87-96be-f98cc353ef85"}
